bed bugs i don't want them so how do i make sure i don't get them eeeewwwwwwwwww okay are we talking true bedbugs or the gross little mites that everyone is talking anout lately true bed bugs are not very common anymore they are decent size bugs easily seen and leave distinct brown marks along the seams of mattresses etc and they bite leaving itchy welts buying used sheets and bedding doesn't mean you'll have bed bugs sheets can be washed in hot water or with bleach and will be fine or they can go in a ziploc bag in the freezer for days and then washed that kills anything you may be worried about you can pick them up by bringing your pillow from home into a hotel or even putting your luggage on or near the bed in a hotel that has them if it is truly bed bugs you are worried about here is the protocol for getting rid of them keeping them away the first step in control is to eliminate the possibility of bed bugs physically climbing over a mattress or bed to feed pull the bed away from shelving or the wall and coat the legs of the bed with a band of vaseline about inches wide use effective means to prevent or exclude bed bugs from the sleeping area this could include keeping a zone around the bed bed bug free by careful examination and removal of bed bugs with a stiff brush and vacuum and by caulking cracks double sided carpet tape may be effective in trapping bed bugs and excluding them from sleeping areas rather than replacing one mattress with another that is also likely to become infested consider encasing the mattress with a bed bug tight cover bed bugs inside the cover will be unable to feed and will die out since freezing weather will kill bed bugs you may be able to place suspect furniture outdoors during the winter for a period of time to eliminate an infestation do not bring used furniture into the home unless it can be visually inspected in side and out as bed bug free that said here is some info on dust mites which are far more common follow the link and click on the dust mites bar i warn you it's gross keep in mind most info on the web is put out there by companies peddling products or devices to clean away mites so it's their job to make sure it sounds as horrible as possible in reality these mites are harmless unless you have allergies to them do not bite humans and have been around longer than us that being said read on http www technoplaz com pages pagedustmites htm whichever bugs have you skeeved out good luck and hope this helped Diseases of the honeybee Brewery Fancy rat House dust mite Upholstery Waterbed Drill bit Floppy disk Top-bar hive Bed (furniture) Menstrual cup Episodes of Lost (Season 1) Social rule Strap-on dildo Cat Plastic Dairy Vacuum mattress RuneScape quests Pillow Textile manufacturing Mosquito Software bug First aid Gramophone record Carpet Cascading Style Sheets Dog training The Hitchhiker's Guide to the Galaxy Tertiary to Quintessential Phases Poker jargon Hamster Diablo II: Lord of Destruction Mouse (computing) Equine conformation Naruto jutsu Allergy Vacuum cleaner American and British English differences The Amber Spyglass Roomba Combine (Half-Life 2) Genericized trademark Welding Avenue Q Textile manufacturing terminology Glossary of climbing terms Glossary of nautical terms Piccolo Junior Saga The Fairly OddParents Insomnia Gaia Online StarCraft Secret Missions Opera (web browser) Gross domestic product Harry Potter and the Prisoner of Azkaban Wget Guinea pig Animal Crossing Bong Protoss Wood Urinary incontinence Main characters of Fullmetal Alchemist The Subtle Knife RuneScape cheats Pok__mon Abilities Sluggy Freelance Tag Hemp Biological pest control Refrigerator ITunes Fecal incontinence Spirit rover timeline for 2004 March Fast bowling Thermal power station Dishwasher Sento Blood Simple Kitchen Professional wrestling match types Casualty lifting Dog agility The Catcher in the Rye Berth Aluminium Pakistani cricket team in West Indies in 2005 Carnivorous plant Carburetor View camera 